Reasoning: The paper deals with the design of precoders and receiver matrices in a MIMO channel with a relay, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The use of a relay also suggests the possibility of networked communication, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The problem of power allocation and constraint is a control engineering problem, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of receiver matrices suggests the possibility of signal processing techniques, which falls under the category of Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the simulation results suggest the possibility of communication engineering, which falls under the category of Computer Engineering (cs.CE).
